Galadari Hotels Lanka Plans to Convert Debt Into Equity

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e
-- 
2011-05-19T09:55:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/galadari-hotels-lanka-plans-to-convert-debt-into-equity.html
Galadari Hotels Lanka Plc (GHLL)  said it
plans to convert about $52 million in debt owed to  Sri Lanka ’s
finance ministry and parent Galadari Brothers Co. into equity in
a bid to boost profitability as the South Asian island’s leisure
industry booms, according to a stock exchange filing.  Galadari Hotels Lanka is seeking regulatory approvals and
valuations for the conversion through a private placement, it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
